<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>98<percent/> of 23</li> 
<li>4<percent/> of 2511</li> 
<li>29<percent/> of 293</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>B: 4<percent/> of 2511</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{98}\%\cdot{23}={22.54}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{29}\%\cdot{293}={84.97}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{4}\%\cdot{2511}={100.44}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 4<percent/> of 2511 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
